{"body": "Scottish Child Payment is a weekly payment of \u00a328.20 that you can get for every child you look after who's under 16 years of age. You'll get the payment every 4 weeks if your application is successful. Only one person can get Scottish Child Payment for a child.", "citation_label": "mygov.scot Scottish Child Payment", "citation_path": "uk/guidance/mygovscot/scottish-child-payment", "document_class": "guidance", "expression_date": "2026-06-10", "heading": "Scottish Child Payment", "id": "372a86ec-8c09-5ba2-8d97-db654f5183c1", "jurisdiction": "uk", "kind": "guidance", "language": "en", "legal_identifier": "mygov.scot Scottish Child Payment", "level": 1, "metadata": {"retrieved_at": "2026-06-10T17:30:00Z"}, "ordinal": 1, "parent_citation_path": "uk/guidance/mygovscot", "source_as_of": "2026-06-10", "source_document_id": "mygovscot/scottish-child-payment", "source_format": "mygov.scot-html", "source_id": "https://www.mygov.scot/scottish-child-payment", "source_path": "", "source_url": "https://www.mygov.scot/scottish-child-payment", "version": "2026-06-10-uk-source-grounding"}
